## Commands Reference

### START Commands
- `/start` - Begin START phase
- `/start requirements` - Work on requirements
- `/start technology` - Work on technology
- `/start architecture` - Work on architecture
- `/start scaffold` - Work on scaffolding
- `/start environment` - Work on environment
- `/start memory` - Initialize memory bank

### RIPER Commands
- `/riper` - Show RIPER status
- `/research` - Enter research phase
- `/innovate` - Enter innovate phase
- `/plan` - Enter plan phase
- `/execute` - Enter execute phase
- `/review` - Enter review phase
- `/next` - Move to next phase
- `/back` - Return to previous phase

### State Commands
- `/state` - Show current state
- `/state phase [phase]` - Set phase
- `/state task [task]` - Set task
- `/state blocker [issue]` - Add blocker

### Memory Commands
- `/memory` - Show memory bank
- `/memory add` - Add entry
- `/memory search [term]` - Search
- `/memory decision` - Log decision
- `/memory pattern` - Document pattern

